<HEADLINE>
PAT KICKER QUITS OVER SIGNING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   EUGENE, Ore. _ Arizona State kicker  &UR; Mike Gauthier quit the team
Friday after learning the Sun Devils had received an oral
commitment from a standout local kicker.
</P>
<P>
   Gauthier, a redshirt freshman who handled extra points, spoke
with Sun Devils Coach  &UR; Bruce Snyder Friday after learning that
Mountain Pointe's  &UR; Mike Barth said he would sign with ASU.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot, 205-pound Barth originally committed to California
but changed his mind and said he wants to play for the Sun Devils.
</P>
<P>
   ASU had to scramble Friday to get a second kicker to back up
 &UR; Stephen Baker for Saturday's game against Oregon. Walk-on  &UR; John
 &UR; Nicassio, a junior from Agoura, Calif., flew to Eugene on Friday
night to join his teammates.
</P>
<P>
   Baker handled all kicking and punting Saturday. He made ASU's
only extra-point attempt and connected on 2 of 3 field-goal
attempts. &QL; 
Heap of talent &QL; 
The Sun Devils had few bright spots, but tight end  &UR; Todd Heap was
one of them.
</P>
<P>
   The freshman had a career high four catches for 99 yards and was
the team's leading receiver.
</P>
<P>
   He made several big plays, including catching a 33-yard pass
late in the game that set up ASU's final touchdown.
</P>
<P>
   He also had a 45-yard catch that led to a Baker 46-yard field
goal in the second quarter and a 15-yard reception that set up
Baker's 22-yard kick in the first. &QL; 
Teammate support &QL; 
 &UR; Steve Campbell said one of his biggest supporters in recent weeks
has been quarterback  &UR; Chad Elliott. Campbell was selected over
Elliott to start in place of the injured  &UR; Ryan Kealy.
</P>
<P>
   ``Chad's got a bad rap,'' Campbell said. ``He's been real good
about it and happy for me when I play. In fact, he was probably
more on the emotional side than any of the other quarterbacks.
(After Campbell's performance against California), he was asking me
more about the feeling and stuff like that.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a real nice kid and well-liked on the team.''
</P>
<P>
   Elliott played a bit in the fourth quarter, completing 5 of 8
passes for 24 yards. &QL; 
Smith backer &QL; 
 &UR; Akili Smith has a supporter in ASU cornerback  &UR; Courtney Jackson,
who respects the Oregon quarterback for more than just his playing
ability.
</P>
<P>
   ``Personally, it's just nice to see a Black quarterback succeed
against the stereotypes often associated with Black quarterbacks:
They're too short, their arm's not strong enough, they can't handle
the position,'' Jackson said. ``For that reason alone, I'm glad to
see he's doing so well.'' &QL; 
Quick hits &QL; 
ASU receiver  &UR; Lenzie Jackson has caught a pass in 35 straight
games.
</P>
<P>
   From the rub-it-in-your face department: After Campbell threw a
pass that went way out of bounds, the Autzen Stadium public address
announcer told the crowd: ``Pass complete to Section 25.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
