<HEADLINE>
AUGUSTINE BACK WITH USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   USC routed the I-Can All-Stars 101-54 in an exhibition game at
the Lyon Center on Saturday night, but the bigger news was that
sophomore point guard Kevin Augustine returned to the team, and
will be in uniform for Tuesday night's season opener against San
Diego State.
</P>
<P>
   Augustine was on the bench Saturday, but did not dress. He said
his recent suspension from the basketball team arose because he was
feeling burned out.
</P>
<P>
   ``After 12 years of playing basketball, it just came to me. Is
this something I want to continue doing? It definitely is,''
Augustine said. ``I just needed some time to clear my head and
refocus. It was never any problems with my teammates or coaches. I
needed to refocus on myself.''
</P>
<P>
   USC coach Henry Bibby said Augustine would be in uniform
Tuesday, but he was unsure if he would play.
</P>
<P>
   As for the exhibition, USC's newcomers put up the most
impressive numbers. Junior-college transfer Quincy Wilder led the
Trojans with 15 points while freshman forward Sam Clancy had 14
points and eight rebounds. Six Trojans were in double figures,
including sophomore center Brian Scalabrine, who had 10 points and
six rebounds.
</P>
</TEXT>
