enter the debris-strewn backwash of the comet Temple-Tuttle and
will then witness the most intense meteor storm in more than three
decades. One international academic organization characterizes the
event as the first meteor threat to satellites in history. The
satellite industry, however, and many of the companies that rely
upon it, have a different reaction: no big deal. By Seth Schiesel.
