<P>
   DUNN-GOP (Washington) _ Late last summer, Rep. Jennifer Dunn,
R-Wash., took a quick trip to Southern California to help out one
of her most endangered colleagues, Rep. Brian Bilbray, a Republican
from La Jolla. Now, as Dunn wages an uphill campaign to become
House majority leader, Bilbray is returning the favor, supporting
Dunn as she takes on the incumbent, Dick Armey of Texas, and the
insurgent, former Seattle Seahawk Steve Largent of Oklahoma. Dunn's
labors on behalf of her fellow Republicans are a major selling
point as she campaigns to become the first woman to hold a top job
in the House.
