   JAPAN-ECON (Tokyo) _ The Japanese government has racheted up to
a monumental $200 billion the size of an economic stimulus package
that it is expected to announce Monday, making this the largest
package Japan has announced in eight years of economic malaise. By
Sheryl WuDunn.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
