</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UNDERDOG USUALLY DOES WELL IN THIS COLLISION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The prevailing theory is that anything can happen
when UCLA and USC collide, but that is not true. Something will
happen. Something specific, something exciting and something
inviting.
</P>
<P>
   If history holds, the underdog will rise.
</P>
<P>
   The underdog has covered the point spread nine years in a row in
the cross-town showdown _ an amazing streak that began when 3-7
UCLA tied the No.8 Trojans in 1989.
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins have been underdogs five times during their
seven-game winning streak and covered the spread each time _
including 1993, when Rose Bowl-bound UCLA was a one-point underdog.
Last year, UCLA was a 10-point favorite and won 31-24.
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins are a 7-point favorite this week.
</P>
<P>
   __ BCS update: The Bruins remained third in the Associated Press
and the ESPN/Coaches' Top-25 polls, but they moved up one spot in
the Sagarin computer ratings.
</P>
<P>
   Expect UCLA to remain No.2 when the Bowl Championship Series
rankings are released today, trailing Tennessee and holding a
narrow lead over Kansas State. Both teams closed ground on the
Volunteers.
</P>
<P>
   __ So close, so far: Tod McBride nearly blocked his third punt
of the season in the fourth quarter at Washington. He charged
through a hole in the protection but missed the ball and was called
for roughing the kicker _ the first such penalty called on the
Bruins this year.
</P>
<P>
   Washington retained possession, but safety Larry Atkins
intercepted Huskies quarterback Brock Huard a few plays later.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't hit him,'' McBride said. ``I guess they called it on
me because I was the only one around, but I didn't touch him.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Decision time?` The Bruins are two wins from a potential
conflict. The Fiesta Bowl is Jan.4 at 5 p.m., but the men's
basketball team is scheduled to play Arizona State that day at 7:30
p.m. at Pauley Pavilion.
</P>
<P>
   There are two obvious options: Move the basketball game to
Jan.3, a Sunday, or keep the game on the 4th but move tipoff to
noon.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, the conflict is moot if the Bruins don't qualify for
the Fiesta Bowl, which explains their reluctance to make a
decision.
</P>
<P>
   __ A reminder: As usual during USC week, practice is closed to
the public.
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury update: Right tackle Brian Polak injured his right
knee during the third quarter but returned a few plays later and is
expected to play this week.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
